# 🎧 GLADIA-BACKEND

This is a Node.js + TypeScript application that allows users to upload audio files and transcribe them using the [Gladia API](https://gladia.io/).

---

## 🌐 Backend URL (Render)

The backend is deployed and accessible at:

👉 [https://audio-text-app.onrender.com]

## 🚀 Getting Started

Follow the steps below to run the project locally after cloning it.

---

## 1. Clone the Repository

## 2. Install Dependencies

npm install

---

## 3. Add Environment Variables

Create a .env file in the root of the project and add the Environment variables:

---

## 4. Create Required Folders

You must create the folder where uploaded audio files will be stored:

tmp/uploads/recordings

---

## 5. Run the Server in Development

To start the server in development mode, run:

npm run dev

---

## 6. Access Uploaded Files

Once an audio file is uploaded, it is stored in the folder:

tmp/uploads/recordings

So the uploaded files can be accessed at:

Locally:
http://localhost:5000/tmp/uploads/recordings/your-audio.wav

On Render:
https://audio-text-app.onrender.com/tmp/uploads/recordings/your-audio.wav

## 7. Swagger API Docs

http://localhost:5000/api-doc
